      <h2 class="section__heading">A Certified ProAdvisor sets up the asset register inside your own books.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Turning on a feature is easy; making the fixed asset register actually trustworthy is the real work. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor decides with you what to capitalize, enters each asset at its correct cost and in-service date, sets sensible useful lives, and configures book depreciation so it posts cleanly &mdash; then reconciles the register&rsquo;s accumulated depreciation to the balance sheet so the detail ties to the statements. Where assets were expensed instead of capitalized, or depreciation was never recorded, we untangle the history against a written scope, inside your own QuickBooks Online file. Tax depreciation &mdash; Section 179, bonus, MACRS &mdash; and the tax return are your CPA&rsquo;s or EA&rsquo;s determination; we give them a clean year-end fixed asset schedule to reconcile against. Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support; an Intuit account, login, or billing matter stays with Intuit.</p>
